u2pdf is a command line utility roughly based upon a2ps that
generates a PDF file reflecting the contents of the input file.
Command line options can be used to remove headings or page
borders or to number the input file lines, or change the
page style (portrait, landscape or 2-up).

This tool is particularly useful when the input file contains
UTF-8 characters such as an APL source file.

This tool is written in python using the cairo, pango and
pangocairo modules to produce the output file.

usage: u2pdf [-h] [-o OUTFILE] [--overwrite] [--pdf | --ps]
             [--paper PAPERSIZE] [--portrait | --landscape | --2up]
             [--tabs TABS] [--number] [--borders | --noborders]
             [--headings | --noheadings] [--font FONTNAME] [--fs FONTSIZE]
             [--lineskip LINESKIP] [--verbose | --quiet] [--test] [--version]
             filename

Prints unicode FILENAME to PDF file.

positional arguments:
  filename              File to be printed.

options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -o OUTFILE, --output OUTFILE
                        Set output PDF file path
  --overwrite, -w       Allow PDF file to be overwritten.
  --pdf, -S             Produce PDF file
  --ps, -s              Produce postscript file
  --paper PAPERSIZE, -P PAPERSIZE
                        Change the default paper size.
  --portrait, -p        View page in portrait mode.
  --landscape, -l       View page in landscape mode.
  --2up, -2             Print two pages per page in landscape mode.
  --tabs TABS, -t TABS  Provide tab stop settings for input file
  --number, -n          Number output lines.
  --borders, -B         Draw borders around page.
  --noborders, -b       Do not draw borders around page.
  --headings, -H        Print page headings.
  --noheadings, -N      Do not include page headings.
  --font FONTNAME, -f FONTNAME
                        Name of font used to display file.
  --fs FONTSIZE, -F FONTSIZE
                        Size in points for font.
  --lineskip LINESKIP   Additional line skip in points.
  --verbose, -v         Display additional information
  --quiet, -q           turn off verbose and do not print summary
  --test, -T            Examine arguments and detect errors
  --version, -V         Display u2pdf version and exit
